programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Clare Moore
programme.desc: A lifetime of neglect has left Clare Moore with no confidence and even less style. With hand-me-down clothes and a home-style hair-cut, Clare's paranoid about her appearance and she should be. Fiona McDonald and her team of experts come to the rescue.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Faith, Hope And Style
programme.desc: Veronica sings in a church choir, but her looks are hitting a sour note. Our doctors will fix her smile and heal her skin. Then, the Glam Squad will lift her spirits with a style makeover. Our mission? To make Veronica look 10 YEARS YOUNGER.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Teacher Learns A Lesson
programme.desc: After a major dental overhaul and LASIK to get rid of her glasses, Patricia is ready for a pop quiz in Beauty 101 from the Glam Squad. Now Patricia can spot the slackers in the back of her classroom, but will she look 10 Years Younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Pandora Ankers
programme.desc: Thanks to a 20-a-day smoking habit, 52-year-old Pandora looks old beyond her years. Can Nicky and the team unleash a younger-looking, happier and more confident Pandora?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Super-Mom, Super Tired
programme.desc: Three kids in three years, a career, and years of sun worshiping has left this super-mom looking less than super. After hi-tech procedures at the dermatologist, a Pilates session, new outfit and makeup, will this mom look 10 years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Felicia Gets Her Groove Back
programme.desc: After the death of both her mother and boyfriend, Felicia is trying to get back her zest for life. She has surrendered to the experts on hand to help her jump back into her old self. Will she rebound for a slam-dunk makeover?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Nerys McGarry
programme.desc: Can the team pull off their biggest challenge to date and make Nerys McGarry - who has lost eight stone - 21 years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Mother Hen To Red Hot Mama
programme.desc: Karen is a mother hen whose chicks have flown the coop. To spice up the future she'll share with her husband, the 10 YEARS YOUNGER team will revamp her appearance – and make her feel beautiful and sexy for the first time in years!
programme.sub-title: From Mother Hen To Red Hot Mama

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Dawn Feeling
programme.desc: At a typically rowdy family breakfast, Rosie is excitedly looking forward to the arrival of her friend Izzy, whilst Danny is concerned about the rumour of ivory poachers in the area. Unnoticed, Miranda the lion cub pads off into the bush.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: The Trevanions have been living at Leopard's Den for over a year. The wildlife is roaming freely and the family are settled into African way of life. Business however is not good. With an abundance of game lodges competition is fierce.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: It's the grand reopening of Mara and a British wildlife charity is using the event to release a vulture back into the wild. Fatani, the new, young and ambitious manager of Mara has hired Danny as the vet to oversee the release.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Leopard's Den is looking after a sick and orphaned baby elephant called Togo. However, despite Evan and Du Plessis' constant vigil, Togo is dying from a broken heart. Evan is distraught and Du Plessis promises they will look after her together.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Sarah's absence couldn't have come at a worse time for Leopard's Den. Nature Conservation is carrying out their annual inspection and everything has to be tip top. Danny's determined they pass with flying colours and everyone is roped in to help.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Everyone's excited at the prospect of Leopard's Den's new arrival. Bash, Danny's old tutor and Rosie's Godfather, is coming from England to help Danny grow his veterinary practice.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: The Trevanions are delighted when Fatani asks Danny to take an aggressive hippo off his hands. As they prepare for its arrival Sarah gets a bit of a shock when her mother Caroline beats the hippo to the post.

programme.title: Perfect Vagina
programme.desc: Through our author's personal journey this documentary will explore this fascinating secret world and question what or who is fuelling women's desire to have perfect vaginas.

programme.title: Tearaway Teen To Beauty Queen: Episode 1
programme.desc: 9 tearaway teens swap hoodies for high heels to battle for a place at a major US teen pageant. First, can beauty queen mentor Michelle Fryatt handle the tears and tantrums when the girls reject a dramatic makeover?

programme.title: Tearaway Teen To Beauty Queen: Episode 2
programme.desc: 8 tearaway teenagers hope to become Miss Teen England International. Their next challenge? Championing a good cause. But after a week's swearing and scrapping can the turbulent teens pull off a convincing speech when put to the test?

programme.title: Tearaway Teen To Beauty Queen: Episode 3
programme.desc: Behaving like a beauty queen proves a tough challenge for the 7 remaining tearaway teens. Mentor Michelle Fryatt expects grace both on and off the catwalk, but shocking bullying and bitching leads to the most explosive elimination yet.

programme.title: Tearaway Teen To Beauty Queen: Episode 4
programme.desc: The 6 remaining wannabe beauty queens face their toughest challenge yet – a full-blown pageant in Manchester. But with stress and stage fright causing explosive outbursts and tearful meltdowns, which three can Michelle risk taking to America as finalists?

programme.title: Tearaway Teen To Beauty Queen: Episode 5
programme.desc: Beauty queen Michelle Fryatt challenges the three remaining teens to survive the media spot light as celebrities – but she didn't mean late night parties and boozing. So will bad behaviour play a part at the elimination in Chicago?

programme.title: Tearaway Teen To Beauty Queen: Episode 6
programme.desc: Beauty Queen Michelle decides which teen deserves to be Miss Teen England. But can her chosen tearaway conquer the US teen professionals and bring home the crown for England at the pageant? Prepare for tears and tantrums...

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 1
programme.desc: Thailand is in a state of political unrest and 41-year-old David, a musician from New South Wales, has just been arrested for overstaying his visa. Can the embassy get him out?

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Historic Ice Trophy / Hyundai / Lancia
programme.desc: The Historic Ice Trophy is attended by many car enthusiasts who don't mind driving their cars on ice and snow. Here, vehicles steeped in history are pushed to their limits.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Lotus Elise vs. Roding Roadster / Planai-Classic Winterrallye
programme.desc: A mountain pass road somewhere in Central Europe. Two lightweight sports cars in a duel: the Lotus Elise and the Roding Roadster.
programme.sub-title: Lotus Elise vs. Roding Roadster / Planai-Classic Winterrallye

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Mercedes
programme.desc: For decades, the Mercedes Sprinter has been regarded as the van par excellence and it is not without reason that it has become the eponym for an entire vehicle class in the German language. Its versatility knows no bounds.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Mitsubishi / Peugeot
programme.desc: Drifting with a four-wheel drive vehicle is a fine art. And nowhere is it better than on snow and ice. During drift training with the Mitsubishi Evo X on the Lungauring in Salzburger Land, we get valuable tips on this subject.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Lada / Seat / Smart / Kia
programme.desc: The Lada Niva first rolled off the production line in 1976. Since then, the Russians have built it virtually unchanged. Why change something that has proven itself for decades in the most diverse regions of the world?

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Toyota
programme.desc: With the Toyota GT 86 from J-Sport, it is noticeable that the company's roots lie in racing. The fans' wish to give the Japanese racer significantly more power nevertheless remained unfulfilled.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Ford / Volvo / Suzuki
programme.desc: Americans like it big and wide. The Ford F-150 is one of those vehicles you wouldn't want to look for a parking space in European cities.

programme.title: Tests, Trends & Action: Volkswagen
programme.desc: Now in its fourth generation on the roads, the Volkswagen Golf's little brother is the most powerful Polo GTI ever. It is aimed at sporty customers who do not want to compromise on everyday utility.

programme.title: Tuning: Alpina / Mercedes
programme.desc: Tuning has to be conspicuous - not for Alpina.The B6 is the best example that Alpina has a penchant for understatement. We tested whether there is more to the Alpina B6 than meets the eye.

programme.title: Tuning: BMW / Chevrolet / Audi
programme.desc: The Kelleners Sport 640i is based on one of the most beautifully designed current 4-door coupés. The tuning forge of racing driver Ralf Kelleners specialises in the conversion of BMWs.

programme.title: Tuning: Dodge / Mini Cooper / Porsche
programme.desc: The Dodge RAM is anything but cute. It is a true beast. The ram is the symbol of the Dodge brand and the eponym for a very special vehicle. The RAM pickup combines robustness and impulsiveness.

programme.title: Tuning: Lamborghini / Porsche / Jaguar
programme.desc: A supercharger from O.CT gives the Lamborghini Huracan, which is by no means underpowered, an additional 200 hp. This makes the super sports car the ultimate street-legal projectile.

programme.title: Classic: Alfa Romeo / Apollo 3500 GT
programme.desc: The mother of all Giuliettas, the "Tipo 750", is now a highly sought-after, albeit rare, model among collectors. We accompany Alfa Romeo expert and collector Hartmut Stöppel with his new Giulietta on his search for the original Giulietta.

programme.title: Classic: Alfa Romeo / Apollo 3500 GT

programme.title: Classic: AMC Pacer / Arabella Classics
programme.desc: Harry decides to take a look at an AMC Pacer on offer just a few kilometres away from him. Known from the film "Wayne's World", the Pacer is now a sought-after classic.

programme.title: Classic: Auto Union Type C in Monte Carlo / Bangkok Classic Car Ride / Bayer K 67 research vehicle

programme.sub-title: Auto Union Type C in Monte Carlo / Bangkok Classic Car Ride / Bayer K 67 research vehicle

programme.title: Classic: Bentley / Borgward Isabella Cabriolet
programme.desc: The Bentley Blower from 1930 is an automotive classic that demands full physical effort from the driver.

programme.title: Classic: BMW

programme.title: Classic: Bugatti / Chevrolet Corvair / Chrysler Airflow
programme.desc: In 1935, the racing driver Gaston Descollas won the most important French long-distance race, the Paris-Nice Rally, in a Bugatti Type 57. Now a German Bugatti specialist sits behind the wheel of this car, as he once did.

programme.title: Classic: Citroën 2CV / Concorso d'Eleganza am Comer See / Studebaker Avanti
programme.desc: In the mid-1930s, Pierre Boulanger, the general manager of Citroën, had the idea of developing a small, practical car tailored to the rural population. At the end of 1937, the development of the world-famous 2CV began.
programme.sub-title: Citroën 2CV / Concorso d'Eleganza am Comer See / Studebaker Avanti

programme.title: Classic: F12 Roadster / Lamborghini
programme.desc: More than 50 years ago, the engineers of the Ingolstadt car manufacturer DKW presented the F 12 Roadster, the last passenger car of the traditional brand.

programme.title: Classic: Jaguar / Fiat
programme.desc: On 15 March 1961, the Jaguar E-Type Coupé was presented to the public at the Geneva Motor Show. The reactions to the extraordinary Jaguar were predominantly positive. In Geneva alone, 500 E-Types were pre-ordered.

programme.title: Classic: Toyota / Renault
programme.desc: The Toyota Land Cruiser is more successful than the off-road vehicles from Mercedes, Land Rover and Co. The Land Cruiser's ease of spare parts procurement makes all the difference. This bush taxi really gets everything and everyone from A to B.

programme.title: Classic: Audi / Der Beradino / Facel Vega Facellia
programme.desc: Audi revolutionised the rally world with the Quattro. We present the rally history of the Audi Quattro from its beginnings in 1980 to its successes in Group B and its victory at Pikes Peak.
programme.sub-title: Audi / Der Beradino / Facel Vega Facellia

programme.title: Classic: Porsche
programme.desc: The Porsche Type 64, of which only three were built, is based on the Volkswagen and produces 35 hp. Due to its aerodynamic shape, the top speed is 160 km/h.

programme.title: Classic: Käfer / Ente / Glas

programme.title: Classic: Josef Stalins ZIS 110 / Melkus RS 1000 / Opel Kapitän 'Kapinator'
programme.desc: James Bond does not yet have a licence to kill when this Russian limousine called ZIS-110 rolls off the production line in 1949. In the 1940s and 50s, this pirated Packard became a popular means of transport for Soviet political celebrities.
